column4: Hi, I asked a few minutes ago about the Lexmark printer driver and how it refuses to actually check to see if it backends.  I've gone into System>Printer, and the status message is "cups-insecure-filter."  Help?
I'd really hate to be pushy or something, but what do I do if my printer says "cups-insecure-filter" as a status?
Never mind about that last one.  Googling it instead.
see if the following bug discussion helps you out at all https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/cups/+bug/436544
